@SG_ML_HEADER_sg_detaileddescription Detailed Description
@SG_ML_L007013SGLHash../cppclass/sglhash provides a hash function struct for use with SGEXTN Containers, this should be used most of the time when using @SG_ML_L00F01BSGLUnorderedSet../cppclass/sglunorderedset, @SG_ML_L014020SGLUnorderedMultiSet../cppclass/sglunorderedmultiset, or @SG_ML_L00F01BSGLUnorderedMap../cppclass/sglunorderedmap. You need hash() defined to use @SG_ML_L00B017SGLEqualsTo../cppclass/sglequalsto with custom structs. @SG_ML_L007013SGLHash../cppclass/sglhash works with all object pointers and C++ builtin types although they do not define hash(). This is a template based class with no separate source file.
@SG_ML_BLANKLINE
@SG_ML_HEADER_sg_implementationdetails Implementation Details
@SG_ML_L007013SGLHash../cppclass/sglhash calls hash() on the corresponding data type if it is a custom struct. If it is a C++ builtin type or a object pointer, @SG_ML_L007013SGLHash../cppclass/sglhash is implemented separately but still works. Implementations of hash() use @SG_ML_L01001CSGLHashAlgorithm../cppclass/sglhashalgorithm.
@SG_ML_BLANKLINE
